    <stitle>INSTRUMENTS - 1000 SERIES Starting 02/08/2004 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - SPEEDOMETER SENSOR</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SPEEDOMETER SENSOR</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0820604">Figure 4</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0820604" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G0820604.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Speedometer Sensor</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SENSOR BODY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LOCKNUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. TRANSMISSION SPEEDOMETER GEAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. SENSOR CONNECTOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Turn the key switch to OFF before removing or installing the speedometer sensor.</para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the sensor connector from the wiring harness connector.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the sensor locknut and remove the sensor from the back of the transmission
                    housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Allison automatic transmissions use a non-adjustable speedometer sensor, but its electrical
                        operation is similar to the standard International sensor.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new sensor by turning into the housing until it bottoms out against the
                    speedometer gear.
                    <emph type="bold">Back off one (1) turn.</emph>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the locknut using two wrenches to keep the sensor from turning while tightening
                    the locknut. Tighten to 15 ft-lbs. (20 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the sensor connector to the wiring harness connector.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Test drive the vehicle to test the speedometer.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
